<p><i><b>Ringworld</b></i> is a <a href="/wiki/Hugo_Award" title="Hugo Award">Hugo</a>, <a href="/wiki/Nebula_Award" title="Nebula Award">Nebula</a>, and <a href="/wiki/Locus_Award" title="Locus Award" class="mw-redirect">Locus</a> award-winning <a href="/wiki/1970_in_literature" title="1970 in literature">1970</a> <a href="/wiki/Science_fiction" title="Science fiction">science fiction</a> novel by <a href="/wiki/Larry_Niven" title="Larry Niven">Larry Niven</a>, set in his <a href="/wiki/Known_Space" title="Known Space">Known Space</a> universe and considered a classic of science fiction literature. It is followed by three sequels, and ties into numerous other books set in Known Space.</p>
